# Get the location of users that are not retweets
locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF <- as.data.frame(screenNames_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF_NotRetweets])
# Remove the empty locations, value of ""
locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF <- locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF[locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF != ""]
# Remove non UTF-8 and ASCII values with internationalization conversion function, main purpose for us to is remove emojis
locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF <- as.data.frame(iconv(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF, "ASCII", "UTF-8", sub=""))
# Remove NA locations
locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF <- as.data.frame(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF[!is.na(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF)])
# Remove empty locations again in case more occurred
locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF <- as.data.frame(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF[locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF != ""])
# Change the column name to location so it is more readable
colnames(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF) <- ("location")

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 1:500){
    # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
    if(counter == 3){
        Sys.sleep(1)
        counter <- 0
    }
    geocoded <- geocode(as.character(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
    counter <- counter + 1
    if(ncol(geocoded) == 3){
        # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
            ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1 <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1, geocoded)
        }
}
ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1DF <- as.data.frame(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1)

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part2 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 501:1500){
    if(!grepl("#", locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[i])){
        # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
        if(counter == 3){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
            }
        geocoded2 <- geocode(as.character(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(geocoded2) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part2 <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part2, geocoded2)
            }
        }
}
ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part2DF <- as.data.frame(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part2)

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part3 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 1501:2500){
    if(!grepl("#", locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[i])){
        # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
        if(counter == 5){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
            }
        geocoded3 <- geocode(as.character(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_WestDF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(geocoded3) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part3 <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part3, geocoded3)
            }
        }
}
ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part3DF <- as.data.frame(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part3)

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1_USA <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
# clean the data practical, get only the USA geocodes
for(i in 1:nrow(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1DF)){
    addr <- ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1DF$address[i]
    split_address <- strsplit(as.character(addr), ",")
    split_address <- as.data.frame(split_address)
    colnames(split_address) <- ("split_addr")
    country <- tail(split_address, 1)
#    print(country$split)
    if(trimws(country$split) == "usa" || trimws(country$split) == "united states"){
        ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1_USA <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1_USA, ll.flu_2_24_3_06_West_part1DF[i,])
    }
}

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 1:2000){
    # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
    if(!grepl("#", locations_flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF$location[i])){
        if(counter == 3){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
        }
        geocoded <- geocode(as.character(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(geocoded) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East, geocoded)
            }
        }
}

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_USA <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
# clean the data practical, get only the USA geocodes
for(i in 1:nrow(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF)){
    addr <- ll.flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF$address[i]
    split_address <- strsplit(as.character(addr), ",")
    split_address <- as.data.frame(split_address)
    colnames(split_address) <- ("split_addr")
    country <- tail(split_address, 1)
#    print(country$split)
    if(trimws(country$split) == "usa" || trimws(country$split) == "united states"){
        ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_USA <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_USA, ll.flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF[i,])
    }
}

ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_part2 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 2001:3800){
    # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
    if(!grepl("#", locations_flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF$location[i])){
        if(counter == 3){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
        }
        geocoded <- geocode(as.character(locations_flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(geocoded) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_part2 <- rbind(ll.flu_2_24_3_06_East_part2, geocoded)
            }
        }
}

    addr <- ll.flu_2_24_3_06_EastDF_part2$address[i]
    split_address <- strsplit(as.character(addr), ",")

    }

# Get the location of users that are not retweets
locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF <- as.data.frame(screenNames_influenza_2_24_3_09DF$location[influenza_2_24_3_09DF_NotRetweets])
# Remove the empty locations, value of ""
locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF <- locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF[locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF != ""]
# Remove non UTF-8 and ASCII values with internationalization conversion function, main purpose for us to is remove emojis
locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF <- as.data.frame(iconv(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF, "ASCII", "UTF-8", sub=""))
# Remove NA locations
locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF <- as.data.frame(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF[!is.na(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF)])
# Remove empty locations again in case more occurred
locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF <- as.data.frame(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF[locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF != ""])
# Change the column name to location so it is more readable
colnames(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF) <- ("location")

ll.influenza_2_24_3_09 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 1:1500){
    if(!grepl("#", locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF$location[i])){
        # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
        if(counter == 3){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
            }
        moregeocoded <- geocode(as.character(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(moregeocoded) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.influenza_2_24_3_09 <- rbind(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09, moregeocoded)
            }
        }
}

ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2 <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
counter <- 0
for(i in 1501:2500){
    if(!grepl("#", locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF$location[i])){
        # Create a counter to deal with the OVER_LIMIT query caused by geocode executing faster than allowed
        if(counter == 3){
            Sys.sleep(1)
            counter <- 0
            }
        moregeocoded <- geocode(as.character(locations_influenza_2_24_3_09DF$location[i]), output = "latlona", source = "google")
        counter <- counter + 1
        if(ncol(moregeocoded) == 3){
            # use rbind to add to a dataframe to prevent loss of data from failure of geocode function
                ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2 <- rbind(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2, moregeocoded)
            }
        }
}

ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF_USA <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
# clean the data practical, get only the USA geocodes
for(i in 1:nrow(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF)){
    addr <- ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF$address[i]
    split_address <- strsplit(as.character(addr), ",")
    split_address <- as.data.frame(split_address)
    colnames(split_address) <- ("split_addr")
    country <- tail(split_address, 1)
#    print(country$split)
    if(trimws(country$split) == "usa" || trimws(country$split) == "united states"){
        ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF_USA <- rbind(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF_USA, ll.influenza_2_24_3_09DF[i,])
    }
}

ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF_USA <- as.data.frame(x = NULL, row.names = NULL)
# clean the data practical, get only the USA geocodes
for(i in 1:nrow(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF)){
    addr <- ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF$address[i]
    split_address <- strsplit(as.character(addr), ",")
    split_address <- as.data.frame(split_address)
    colnames(split_address) <- ("split_addr")
    country <- tail(split_address, 1)
#    print(country$split)
    if(trimws(country$split) == "usa" || trimws(country$split) == "united states"){
        ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF_USA <- rbind(ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF_USA, ll.influenza_2_24_3_09_part2DF[i,])
    }
}
